data.comment: The referee blows his whistle to start the first-half. Eupen with the kick-off.
Gianni Bruno (Zulte) has received a first yellow card.
In the minute 34, Knowledge Musona puts the ball in the net and the home team now lead 1-0.
The first-half has ended.
The second-half has commenced. Zulte with the kick-off.
In the minute 46, The away team have replaced Nikolaos Kenourgios with Bassem Srarfi. This is the first substitution made today by Francky Dury.
Jean-Luc Dompe is replacing Jelle Vossen for Zulte at Kehrweg Stadium.
Ibrahima Seck for Zulte has been booked by Wim Smet and receives a first yellow card.
In the minute 57, Goal! Eupen extend their lead to 2-0 through Knowledge Musona.
Eupen's Menno Koch has been booked in Eupen.
Eupen make their first substitution with Carlos Embalo replacing Isaac Nuhu.
In the minute 68, Mathieu De Smet is on a sub for Omar Govea for Zulte.
Andreas Beck is replacing Jonathan Heris for the home team.
Goal! Zulte reduce the deficit to 2-1 through Jean-Luc Dompe.
In the minute 79, Benat San Jose Gil is making the team's third substitution at Kehrweg Stadium with Mamadou Kone replacing Amara Baby.
Smail Prevljak is on a sub for Knowledge Musona for Eupen.
Konan N'Dri (Eupen) gets a yellow card.
In the minute 82, Goal! Gianni Bruno equalizes to bring the score to 2-2.
Goal! A Olivier Deschacht header gives Zulte a 2-3 lead in Eupen.
Smail Prevljak is booked for the home team.
Full-time! The final score is 2-3.
Abdoulaye Sissako is replacing Gianni Bruno for the away team.
